&lt;p&gt;you can see the available lexers under html5css3/thirdparty/prettify/lang-<problematic ids="id24" refid="id23">*</problematic>.js&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="revealjs-notes"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;RevealJs Notes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to print pass --reveal-js-opts printpdf=true, for example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
rst2html5 --jquery --reveal-js --reveal-js-opts printpdf=true examples/slides.rst &amp;gt; reveal-print.html
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;this can be used to open with chrome or chromium and print as pdf as described here: &lt;a class="reference external" href="<reference refuri="https://github.com/hakimel/reveal.js#pdf-export">https://github.com/hakimel/reveal.js#pdf-export</reference>"&gt;https://github.com/hakimel/reveal.js#pdf-export&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="math-support"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Math Support&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;math&lt;/tt&gt; role and directive to include inline math and block-level equations into your document:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
When :math`a ne 0`, there are two solutions to <math>ax^2 + bx + c = 0</math>
and they are</paragraph><system_message backrefs="id24" ids="id23" level="2" line="382" source="outputHTML.html" type="WARNING"><paragraph>Inline emphasis start-string without end-string.</paragraph></system_message><math_block xml:space="preserve">x = {-b \pm \sqrt{b^2-4ac} \over 2a}</math_block><system_message level="2" line="504" source="outputHTML.html" type="WARNING"><paragraph>Explicit markup ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent.</paragraph></system_message><paragraph>&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both of these support a basic subset of &lt;a class="reference external" href="<reference refuri="https://www.latex-project.org">https://www.latex-project.org</reference>"&gt;LaTeX&lt;/a&gt; syntax.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By default, &lt;a class="reference external" href="<reference refuri="https://www.mathjax.org">https://www.mathjax.org</reference>"&gt;MathJax&lt;/a&gt; is used for displaying math. You can choose a different output format using the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--math-output&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; command line option:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--math-output&lt;/span&gt; mathjax&lt;/tt&gt; uses MathJax (the default)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--math-output&lt;/span&gt; html&lt;/tt&gt; will use plain HTML + CSS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--math-output&lt;/span&gt; mathml&lt;/tt&gt; will use &lt;a class="reference external" href="<reference refuri="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MathML">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MathML</reference>"&gt;MathML&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--math-output&lt;/span&gt; latex&lt;/tt&gt; outputs raw LaTeX&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you use MathJax, you can use the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--mathjax-url&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;-mathjax-config&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; command line options to configure a custom MathJax JavaScript URL and to provide a file with a custom MathJax configuration, respectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you use HTML + CSS output, you can use the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--math-css&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; command line option to configure a custom math stylesheet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note that the old MathJax postprocessor (activated using &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;--mathjax&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;) has been deprecated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
